===Etymology 2===
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|たて|alt=舘}}

Likely derived from {{ja-r|建て|たて}}, the {{ja-ryk|建てる|たてる|to [[erect]] a [[structure]]|nodot=y}}, in turn from the verb {{ja-r|立つ|たつ|to [[stand]], to [[stand up]]}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref><ref name="DJR">{{R:Daijirin}}</ref>

The reading ''tate'' is most common in eastern Japan, correlating to the ''tachi'' reading in western Japan.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref><ref name="DJR">{{R:Daijirin}}</ref>

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|たて|acc=1|acc_ref=DJR,SMK7}}

====Noun====
{{ja-noun|たて}}

# a large [[building]]
# a [[mansion]], a [[villa]], an [[estate]]
# {{lb|ja|sort=たて|honorific|archaic}} a form of address or reference for a [[noble]]
# a small [[castle]] or [[fort]]

